metadata.name: Lists GET /api/v1/lists returns the expected lists

sql_query.sql: SELECT 1 AS one FROM "oauth_access_tokens" WHERE "oauth_access_tokens"."token" = $1 LIMIT $2
SELECT 1 AS one FROM "oauth_access_tokens" WHERE "oauth_access_tokens"."token" = $1 AND "oauth_access_tokens"."id" != $2 LIMIT $3

return_value.value: [{id=>667, title=>first list, replies_policy=>followed, exclusive=>false}, {id=>668, title=>second list, replies_policy=>list, exclusive=>false}, {id=>669, title=>third list, replies_policy=>none, exclusive=>false}, {id=>670, title=>fourth list, replies_policy=>list, exclusive=>true}]
